Правило: Не нужно оптимизировать то, что пока не работает.
Создадим базовое дерьмо, потом же подумаем, что делать.
I nivelo

Noun (N): -o
Article (D): la
Adjective (A): -a
Present Verb(PV): -as
Numeral (NUM): POSX(NUM)
Conj (CONJ) : kaj 
Dot (DOT) : .

Artcile (ART) :- D | e
Full Noun (FN) :- ART + AN
Adjective group (AG) :- A + AG | e
Adjective noun (AN) :- AG + N | N + AG (AG = Attributive Adjective)
Stem (S) :- PV + FN | FN + PV
Additional Stem (AS) :- KAJ + S + AS | e
Sent(SENT) :- S + AS + DOT | NUM + DOT | FN + DOT

Extraxting Attributive Adjectives, we can unserstand, Which properties can objects have!

II nivelo
Plural Noun (PN) : -oj
Plural Adjective (PA) : -aj
Predicative Verb (PRV) : estas,  sxajnas (not all verbs are predicative!)
Prep (PREP):- sur | en

Plural Full Noun (PFN) :- ART + PAN
Plural Adjective group (PAG) :- PA + PAG | e
Plural Adjective noun (PAN) :- PAG + PN | PN + PAG (PAG = Attributive Adjective)
Stem (S) :- PV + NG | NG + PV | NG (N = subjective, PV - ROOT)
NG (Noun Group) :- PFN | UFN + CONJ + UFN 
UFN (Undefined Full Noun) :- PFN | FN

Predicative Stem (PS) :- FN + PRV + A | NG + PRV + PA | FN + PRV + AN | PFN + PRV + PAN |

Predicate (PRED) :- ARG SUBJ ARG PRV ARG OBJ ARG 
Plural Predicate (PPRED) :- ARG PSUBJ ARG PRV ARG POBJ ARG
SUBJ :- FN
PUBJ :- PS
Predicate Argument (ARG) :- PREP + FN + ARG | e
